This paper is likely to belong to the category of Computer Science - Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) as it proposes a new security protocol to mitigate a class of attacks known as code-reuse attacks. Additionally, the paper discusses the need for redesigning virtual memory to increase system security, which falls under the category of computer security. 

It could also belong to the category of Computer Science - Architecture (cs.AR) as it proposes a new microarchitectural adjustment to enhance system security. 

Computer Science - Software Engineering (cs.SE) is another likely category as the paper discusses the implementation of a new security feature that requires minor adjustments to the microarchitecture. 

Computer Science - Programming Languages (cs.PL) is a possible category as the paper proposes a new way of assigning names to data objects and instructions, which could be considered a language feature. 

Lastly, Computer Science - Systems and Control (cs.SY) is a possible category as the paper proposes a new system design to enhance security.
